args:
Bahamut is attempting to destroy the world in
an effort to stave off the Progenitor's return.
Learning this, the prince and his friends decide
to head into the world of Nedrick's mind in
order to save his body and aid in the fight.
It's Nedrick!\nHe's shifted back to human form...
By his own accord or not, I wonder.
You mustn't let your guard down;\nI still sense a frightfully strong level\nof Bahamut's presence within him.
Perhaps it really was the dragon's power\neating away at him.
One thing is certain: He's definitely not in\ntop form. And that's why we can't let this\nopportunity pass us by.
You take me too lightly; I can defeat the\nlot of you without breaking a sweat no\nmatter my condition.

Oh, but I'm not taking you lightly at all.
I know well how strong you are, which is
why we must take this chance to end
things once and for all.
Please don't suggest I stay my hand out\nof some misguided sense of pity, Brother.
Chelle, our goal is to stop Nedrick,\nnot to kill him.
We're going to have to fight the Progenitor\nat some point, and Nedrick would be a\nvaluable ally in that battle.
This line of thought is not without merit,\nbut a future threat is insufficient reason\nto ignore a present danger.
But there's no telling what will happen\nto Bahamut if we kill Nedrick now.
He shapeshifted! Is he going to try \nsettling things with us here and now?!
This is different. It... No. It cannot be!
Okay, now he's opening a rift thingie,\nand those are NEVER good.
Zethia? What are you talking about?
Bahamut is a wyrm of creation, yes...\nbut he is also one of destruction.
His power can erase existence itself.
It makes sense that the being who created\nthe world has the ability to destroy it.\nBut the problem isâ€”
Hang on a hot freakin' second there, bub!\nYou think this joker's gonna end the world?\nLike, the WORLD world?!
Nedrick would never consider such a thing.
Unless his consciousness has already\nbeen seized by Bahamut.
You're right! Bahamut's going to destroy\nthe entire world if this keeps up!
But why would he even WANT to do that?!
Isn't he the dude who created it in the first\nplace? Why does he want to trash it?!
AAAAAAAH! NO, BAHAMUT!\nI WILL NOT PERMIT THIS!
Yes... Bahamut's control was...stronger\nthan I expected, but I am myself again...
Tell us what's going on, Nedrick.
We know Bahamut is trying to destroy the\nworld, but we don't understand why.
Bahamut thinks the Progenitor will return,\nand the conditions for that to happen in\nthis world are now perfect.
What conditions? What is it that will let\nthe Progenitor come back?

There are more conditions than you can
fathom. But a major factor is that someone
siding with the Progenitor has used the
Other's power.

Another is the activity of the ones known
as ï¼‚demons,ï¼‚ and yet another is that
Elysiumâ€”the very custodian of the worldâ€”
has been corrupted by black mana.
It's also not wholly unrelated to the fact\nthat Bahamut has a bodyâ€”which is to say\nhe has me.
Amongst all the worlds of possibility,\nthis one has become the most fitting\nplace for the return of the Progenitor.
So Bahamut is going to destroy the world\njust to eliminate the possibility of the\nProgenitor's return?!
Exactly. After all, to him this world\nis but one of many possibilities.
That he thinks on such a scale and acts\nwith such ruthlessness befits the Wyrm\nof Genesis, I suppose.
But what about all the people living here?!
If the world is ended, it will be the death\nknell for all life which resides inside it.
I will not permit that to happen. Instead,\nI will subjugate Bahamut and take full\npossession of his power.
I do hope you don't think we're just going\nto leave that little matter in your capable\nhands at this point?
I repeat my strong belief that our most\nefficient path forward is to slay you here\nand now and take Bahamut with you.
Stop. You would only hinder Nedrick\nand hasten Bahamut's return.
Then what ought we do? From our\nperspective, the outcome is foul\nno matter who emerges victorious.
It isn't. You must understand that there\nis a gulf as wide as an ocean between\nNedrick and Bahamut.
I don't imagine we'll have the luxury of\ndiscourse with the wyrm, for one...

But there is no guarantee Nedrick can
best Bahamut, so the most pragmatic
response would be to destroy the body
he now controls.
So then, a proposalâ€”or perhaps it would\nbe better to call it a request.
I have the means to aid Nedrick in the\nstruggle with Bahamut over his body.
If you help me with that, the odds of him\ndefeating Bahamut grow considerably.
I don't need people meddling in this, Jin!\nI will force Bahamut to yield on my own,\njust as I told you I would!
This is unlike you, Nedrick. If you think\nabout it calmly, you would realize what\nmust be done now.

I don't know why you've latched on to
this idea, but what makes you strong is
your ability to cast aside such things
for the sake of our greater goal.
Assuming we go along with this request,\nhow do you intend to compensate us?
By anything within my means to provide.\nYou may ask for the throne of the Faerie\nKingdom or even my lifeâ€”it matters not.
Then here is my request: Abandon your\nplan to give the power of shapeshifting\nto everyone.

Then work with us to come up with a way
to oppose the Progenitor that doesn't
entail the deaths of countless innocent
people. That's what I ask.
Personally, I'd hold out for that throne you\nso kindly offered, but alas, it's not my call.\n...So then? What say you?
My method was the result of thinking\nlong and hard on what would cause\nthe fewest casualties.
Though you clearly think me a monster,\nI would not make a flippant choice that\nwould hurt innocent people unnecessarily.
But what if we can come up with a\nbetter idea that saves MORE lives?!\nWill you consider it then?!
If it is a valid plan, then yes.
I'm going to accept Jinlorda's proposal,\neveryone. We're going to help Nedrick\nfight Bahamut.
I would be lying if I said I didn't have\nmisgivings, Brother, but if that is your\nconclusion, I will accept it.
Yeah! We'll kick his butt together!
I offer my own thanks as well, and give\nmy utmost respect to your decision.
Thanks, Jinlorda. So what do we do now?
Put simply, you will go into the world\nof Nedrick's mind and face Bahamut.
Yes. And for that purpose, I must separate\nyour own spirits from your bodies.
So I may not be a medical professional,\nbut I'm pretty sure separating a spirit from\na body IS HOW YOU KILL SOMEBODY!

Worry not. When all is taken care of,
you will be able to return unharmedâ€”
so long as your spirits are not eliminated
while in the world of his mind, that is.
I DO NOT LIKE THE CAVEAT AT THE END\nOF THAT SENTENCE, MAN!
